{
  "texts": [
    "However, it may be sub-optimal for system performance because the effects among different blocks are not considered.",
    "On the contrary, AI-based methods offer an E2E system design approach, and all blocks of the system can be jointly optimized, showcasing the potential in system-level performance enhancement [215].",
    "For instance, a typical communication system can be modeled as an auto-encoder and all the blocks are represented by a neural network, facilitating the system-level design.",
    "However, this approach often requires a large number of samples to train the AI model, hindering its applications in some scenarios with limited samples.On the other hand, the model-based system design usually optimizes each block of the system based on the specific channel model [216].",
    "Nevertheless, the adopted channel model may not match the actual channel owing to the dynamic environment and difficulty of channel estimation, resulting in performance degradation."
  ]
}